    public class MaterialProgressBar
extends android.widget.ProgressBar
    A ProgressBar subclass that handles tasks related to backported progress drawable.

        public void setShowTrack(boolean showTrack)

      • setProgressTintList

        public void setProgressTintList(@Nullable
                                android.content.res.ColorStateList tint)
        Applies a tint to the progress drawable. Does not modify the current tint mode, which is PorterDuff.Mode#SRC_IN by default.

        Subsequent calls to View.setBackground(Drawable) will automatically mutate the drawable and apply the specified tint and tint mode using Drawable.setTintList(ColorStateList).

        Overrides:
        setProgressTintList in class android.widget.ProgressBar
        Parameters:
        tint - The tint to apply, may be null to clear tint.
        See Also:
        getProgressTintList(), Drawable.setTintList(ColorStateList)
